South Africa s power system has progressed to a position of surplus capacity opening opportunities to extend regional interconnections and to accommodate a changing power generation mix to grow the country s economy Eskom said on Saturday. The electricity parastal said it had committed itself to continue its investment in transmission infrastructure and to leverage advanced technology solutions for a reliable and sustainable power grid. Managing the largest capacity expansion project in Africa Eskom has invested approximately R12 billon in transmission infrastructure and strengthening projects since 2014 to the end of September 2016. More than 6 000 km of transmission lines and 32 000 MVA of substation transformer capacity has been installed since 2005 the power provider said.